    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-08-27T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-08-27T10:00:00-05:00" n="475"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">674.84A/8–2752: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 475<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Israel (<persName corresp="#p_DMB1"
                            type="from">Davis</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d475fn1">Repeated to Cairo and London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-08-27T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 27, 1952—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>320. In view proneness Israelis permit ill-advised leaks of kind referred to in
                    Cairo’s 479,<note n="2" xml:id="d475fn2">
                        <ref target="#d474">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> I propose speak to <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>
                    soon, expressing as my personal view that chance favorable outcome Israel
                    initiative reported <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 304<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d475fn3">
                        <ref target="#d472">Document 472</ref>.</note> may have been prejudiced by
                    publicity reported <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 310<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d475fn4">
                        <ref target="#d473">Document 473</ref>.</note> and any leaks re initiative
                    actually taken wld be contemplated make favorable Egypt action impossible.<note
                        n="5" xml:id="d475fn5">
                        <p>The Department responded on Aug. 28 as follows:</p>
                        <p>“Dept fully approves ur speaking to <gloss target="#t_FonMin1"
                                >FonMin</gloss> along lines <gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                                >Embtel</gloss> 320. You may wish in great confidence inform <gloss
                                target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> we have recently taken occasion
                            remind Egypts US interest in achievement peace with Israel. However, it
                            shld be emphasized that any proclivity towards ‘crowing’ by Israel wld
                            be fatal to such small indications as now exist re favorable attitude
                                <persName corresp="#p_MMA1">Maher</persName> on this problem.”
                            (Telegram 214 to Tel Aviv, Aug. 28, 2:51 p.m.; 674.84A/8–2852)</p>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DMB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
